## Microservices Architecture

This project uses a microservices architecture.

### Service boundaries

- Each service owns its own data store; no direct cross-service database queries
- Cross-service communication via async events (preferred) or synchronous HTTP/gRPC
- Each service is independently deployable; changes to one service must not require coordinated deploys

### API design

- Version all public APIs; never break existing consumers without a migration path
- Return consistent error shapes: `{ code, message, details }` or equivalent
- Use OpenAPI/Protobuf specs as the source of truth for service contracts

### Observability

- Propagate trace context (`traceparent`) across all outbound calls
- Log with structured JSON; include `service`, `trace_id`, `span_id` on every log line
- Expose `/health` and `/ready` endpoints on every service
